tion for the neutron source anisotropy. Correction
for the flux attenuation of incoming and outgoing
neutron within the sample. Correction for the multiple
scattering calculated with the neutron transport code
more and with ENDF/B-IV data.
*By authors*.Measurements of TOF-spectra are carried
out for angle from 15-degree to 150-degree in steps of
15-degree.
The source strength is determined by counting
the alpha-particles of the source reaction with a
silicon surface-barrier detector at an angle 166
degree with respect to the deuteron beam direction.
A scintillation detector and a long counter are
used as relative monitors.
The neutron TOF-detector consists of a liquid
Ne-213 scintillator. The neutron detector efficiency
is measured by tof-spectrometry of Cf-252 fission
neutrons, by a TOF-neutron scattering experiment at
hydrogen using a thin polyethylene ring as well as by
the spectrometry of 14-MeV neutrons from the non-
shadowed neutron source.

regime with deutron pulses of 2-ns fwhm and repetition
rates of 2.5 or 5-mhz, respectively, produced 2....5*
e+09 neutrons/S on a tit-target for a mean deuteron
beamcurrent of 30-mua.
*En-rsl* the angular resolution are less than 4-degree
in the whole angular range. The energy resolution is
3% at 3-MeV emission energy and 7% at 14-MeV.
